&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be part of company that values your skills and expertise?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then you should consider an opportunity with one of New Zealanders largest integrated apple growers, Mr Apple. &amp;nbsp;We have orchards across Hawke’s Bay and opportunities available at different levels depending on your skills, experience and expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you know your way around apple orchards, you’ll recognise what’s needed each day to get the job done right. At Mr Apple, you’ll work alongside experienced growers who are ready to help you sharpen your skills and learn new approaches. Your focus will be making sure the orchard runs smoothly and efficiently, so every season delivers top results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work changes with the seasons—tree care, orchard maintenance, and training others are all part of the role. Safety matters here, and you’ll be expected to set the standard, showing the team what it means to work smart and safe every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have the chance to use the latest technology and try new tools and systems. If you’re keen to improve how things are done and get involved with automation, you’ll find plenty of opportunities to put your ideas to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in horticulture or strong transferable experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in communication, organisation, and time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interested in learning and adapting to new changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic, reliable, and proactive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy working outdoors and being hands-on&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re reliable and so is your transport&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible to work in New Zealand and able to pass pre-employment checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional development and career growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A competitive hourly wage and the stability of a permanent career within a NZ listed company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access industry-leading technology designed to optimise your workplace and enhance productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cutting-edge technology, ensuring we continue to set industry benchmarks and standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to integrity and respect, where high standards are not just met but lived every day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for two skilled Workshop Technicians to join our high performing Engineering &amp;amp; Orchard Support teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Central Hawke’s Bay (CHB) – Senior Workshop Technician&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hastings/Whakatu – Workshop Technician&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re mechanically minded, solutions focused, and enjoy working across a wide range of machinery in a dynamic horticultural environment, this is your next opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Servicing and maintaining company vehicles, tractors, orchard machinery, and plant equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carrying out preventative and corrective maintenance programmes, often on-site across Mr Apple orchards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnosing faults by observing machinery in operation and using diagnostic, measuring, and testing tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing minor repairs and maintenance to keep equipment running efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring all maintenance documentation, MEX requisitions, and work orders are completed accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing the MEX training programme and following all permit processes (hot work, working at heights, confined spaces).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining a tidy, organised workshop, work vehicle, and tool storage areas using 5S standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing operator training and support to orchard teams when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working safely at all times and actively contributing to safety meetings, investigations, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in rostered call outs outside normal hours when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For both roles:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A trade certificate (Agricultural Machinery preferred) or equivalent experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years’ experience working with tractors, agricultural machinery, and light diesel vehicles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong engineering and welding skills (MIG, ARC, TIG).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good physical fitness – the role involves bending, lifting, and twisting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently while being a strong team player.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence using computer based preventative maintenance systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A full manual driver’s licence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to safe work practices, hazard reporting, and following all company procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the Senior CHB role (additional expectations):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years’ experience in a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to provide technical leadership, work autonomously and influence best practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem solving capability and confidence managing complex machinery issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A mobile workshop van for work use when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A stable permanent Monday–Friday schedule, with occasional call outs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work with a wide variety of machinery in a large, innovative horticultural business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive team culture with ongoing training and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A role where your ideas, initiative, and technical expertise are valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to grow your career within New Zealand’s leading apple producer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you&#39;re interested in becoming part of our dynamic team, please indicate in your cover letter which role you are applying for—or let us know if you&#39;re open to being considered for both.&lt;/p&gt;
